2 HOUSE BILL 582
1 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
2 Article – Alcoholic Beverages and Cannabis
3 26–102.
4 This title applies only in Prince George’s County.
5 26–1004.
6 (a) There is a Class C (country club) beer, wine, and liquor license.
7 (b) An application for the license shall be signed by at least one officer of the
8 country club who is a resident[, registered voter,] and taxpayer.
9 26–1005.
10 (a) There is a Class C (country and golf club) beer, wine, and liquor license.
11 (b) An application for the license shall be signed by at least one officer of the
12 country and golf club who is a resident[, registered voter,] and taxpayer of the county.
13 26–1008.
14 (a) There is a Class B/ECF (educational conference facility) beer, wine, and liquor
15 license for the University College Center for Adult Education of the University of Maryland.
16 (b) The Board may issue the license to an individual who is:
17 (1) authorized by the University College Center for Adult Education to:
18 (i) act on its behalf;
19 (ii) assume all responsibility; and
20 (iii) be subject to all the penalties, conditions, and restrictions
21 imposed on licenses; and
22 (2) a resident [and registered voter] of the county.
23 26–1009.
24 (a) There is a Class B–ECF/DS (Education Conference Facility/Dining Service)
25 beer, wine, and liquor license.
26 (b) The Board may issue the license to an individual who is:

HOUSE BILL 582 3
1 (1) (i) authorized by the University of Maryland, College Park Campus
2 to:
3 1. act on its behalf under the license; and
4 2. be subject to the penalties, conditions, and restrictions
5 under this title; and
6 (ii) a resident [and registered voter] of the county; or
7 (2) (i) authorized by the Prince George’s Community College Main
8 Campus to:
9 1. act on its behalf under the license; and
10 2. be subject to the penalties, conditions, and restrictions
11 under this title; and
12 (ii) a resident [and registered voter] of the county.
13 26–1019.
14 (a) There is a Class C (yacht club) beer, wine, and liquor license.
15 (b) The application for the license shall be signed by at least one officer of the
16 yacht club who is a resident[, registered voter,] and taxpayer of the county.
17 26–1405.
18 (a) This section does not apply to:
19 (1) a racetrack license;
20 (2) a Class BLX license;
21 (3) an arena license;
22 (4) a Class BCE (catering) license;
23 (5) a Class B–CC (convention center) license;
24 (6) a Class B/ECF (educational conference facility) license;
25 (7) the issuance, renewal, or transfer of Class B–DD (development district)
26 licenses; or
27 (8) a business whose stock or interest is authorized for sale by the United

4 HOUSE BILL 582
1 States Securities and Exchange Commission.
2 (c) (1) This subsection does not apply to a Class B–Stadium (baseball stadium)
3 beer, wine, and liquor license, a 7–day Class B–ECR on–sale beer, wine, and liquor license,
4 or a Class B–WPL (waterfront pavilion) beer, wine, and liquor license.
5 (2) To be eligible to receive a license, a partner shall[:
6 (i)] be a resident of the State at the time the application is filed and
7 continue to be a resident as long as the license is in effect[; and
8 (ii) be a registered voter of the State].
9 26–1406.
10 (a) This section does not apply to:
11 (1) a racetrack license;
12 (2) a Class BLX license;
13 (3) an arena license;
14 (4) a Class BCE (catering) license;
15 (5) a Class B–CC (convention center) license;
16 (6) a Class B/ECF (educational conference facility) license;
17 (7) the issuance, renewal, or transfer of Class B–DD (development district)
18 licenses; or
19 (8) a business whose stock or interest is authorized for sale by the United
20 States Securities and Exchange Commission.
21 (c) (1) This subsection does not apply to a Class B–Stadium (baseball stadium)
22 beer, wine, and liquor license, a 7–day Class B–ECR on–sale beer, wine, and liquor license,
23 or a Class B–WPL (waterfront pavilion) beer, wine, and liquor license.
24 (2) To be eligible to receive a license, an applicant shall[:
25 (i)] be a resident of the State at the time the application is filed and
26 continue to be a resident as long as the license is in effect[; and
27 (ii) be a registered voter of the State].

